parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the wiring harness can cause electrical system failures, leading to loss of critical vehicle functions, such as lighting, engine, and safety systems, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: corrosion or damage to wiring components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A corroded brake pedal can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A rusted frame and unsecured seat can cause the seat to break away from the frame in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat is loose or unstable
the seat is not properly secured to the frame
the frame is rusted or corroded.

symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the tail light
melted or damaged tail light assembly
